            . I am a <rs id="t18310407-267-viclabel1427" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-267-victim1855 t18310407-267-viclabel1427"></join>, and live in the Hampstead-road. The prisoner has worked for me, off and on, for seven or eight years - I have missed various tools, and gave him in charge last July, for stealing a stock, but could not trace it to him - I still continued to miss tools, and the week before I gave him in charge, he acknowledged having stolen 2 saws, and promised to redeem them - I discharged him, but he did not leave - I found him in my kitchen on Sunday morning, drunk, and gave him in charge - my rule and duplicates for several tools were found on him - I found a quantity of my property at the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>HENRY EAST. I am an officer. I found a number of duplicates on the prisoner; one was for a plane.</p>

